vector<int> vec(1000);

counting = 0;
val = 0;
vcount=0;
radius = 10;
n=0;


while (counting<1000) // assignment of fixed point
{
	xref = x[(counting)];
	yref = y[(counting)];
	{
		while (vcount < 1000) // run comparison of entire vector with the fixed point
		{
			if (xref != x[(vcount)]) && (yref != y[(vcount)]) && (xref+radius >= x[(vcount)]) && (xref-radius <= x[(vcount)]) && (yref+radius >= y[(vcount)]) && (yref-radius <= y[(vcount)])
			{
				val = val + v[(vcount)];
				n++;
			}
		vcount++;
		}
		if (v[(counting)]==1) && (val>0) && (val==n)
		{
		ref=1;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==1) && (val>0)
		{	
		ref=2;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==1) && (val==0)
		{
		ref=3;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==1) && (val<0) && (val==-n)
		{
		ref=5;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==1) && (val<0)
		{	
		ref=4;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==-1) && (val>0) && (val==n)
		{
		ref=6;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==-1) && (val>0)
		{	
		ref=7;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==-1) && (val==0)
		{
		ref=8;
		}
		else
		if (v[(counting)]==-1) && (val<0 && val==-n)
		{
		ref=10;
		}
		else
		ref=9;
		}
	fill_n(vec.begin() + counting, ref)
    counting++;
	}
